HANDBOOK-007

Title:
Database Standards

Version:
1.0

Status:
Official

Project:
NEXOTFE ERP Industrial

==========================================================
PURPOSE
==========================================================

This document defines the official database standards for NEXOTFE.

Every table, column, relationship and constraint must follow these standards.

Database consistency is mandatory.

==========================================================
DATABASE PHILOSOPHY
==========================================================

The database represents the industrial business.

It does not represent screens.

It does not represent pages.

It does not represent React components.

Every table exists because a real business entity exists.

==========================================================
TABLE CLASSIFICATION
==========================================================

Tables are classified into:

• Master Data

• Transactional Data

• Configuration

• System

Every table must belong to one category.

==========================================================
MASTER DATA
==========================================================

Examples:

Customers

Suppliers

Employees

Products

Raw Materials

Resources

Resource Groups

Master Data is stable.

It is referenced by multiple business processes.

==========================================================
TRANSACTIONAL DATA
==========================================================

Examples:

Projects

Quotations

Commercial Proposals

Purchase Requests

Purchase Orders

Inventory Movements

Production Orders

Transactional tables record business events.

==========================================================
STANDARD FIELDS
==========================================================

Every business table must contain:

id

empresa_id

created_at

updated_at

created_by

Whenever applicable:

ativo

deleted_at

deleted_by

These fields are official standards.

==========================================================
PRIMARY KEYS
==========================================================

Every table uses UUID.

Sequential numeric identifiers are never used as Primary Keys.

==========================================================
FOREIGN KEYS
==========================================================

Foreign Keys represent real business relationships.

Never create relationships without business justification.

==========================================================
NAMING STANDARD
==========================================================

Tables:

Plural.

Examples:

clientes

fornecedores

produtos

projetos

Columns:

Singular.

Examples:

cliente_id

produto_id

fornecedor_id

empresa_id

Use snake_case.

Never mix languages.

==========================================================
DATA TYPES
==========================================================

Choose the most appropriate type.

UUID for identifiers.

TEXT for descriptions.

BOOLEAN for logical states.

NUMERIC for quantities and monetary values.

TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE for dates.

Avoid generic fields.

==========================================================
SOFT DELETE
==========================================================

Business records are never physically removed.

Logical deletion is the standard.

Use:

ativo

deleted_at

deleted_by

Physical DELETE is exceptional.

==========================================================
AUDIT
==========================================================

Every important business action must be traceable.

Always preserve:

Creation.

Modification.

Logical deletion.

Responsible user.

==========================================================
MULTI-COMPANY
==========================================================

Business data belongs to one company.

Use empresa_id consistently.

Never allow one company to access another company's data.

==========================================================
INDEXES
==========================================================

Indexes must improve performance.

Typical indexes include:

empresa_id

ativo

created_at

updated_at

Business search fields

Avoid unnecessary indexes.

==========================================================
CONSTRAINTS
==========================================================

Use constraints to protect business integrity.

Examples:

Required fields.

Unique values.

Valid references.

Valid business states.

Business consistency is more important than application validation.

==========================================================
MIGRATIONS
==========================================================

Every structural change must be performed through migrations.

Never edit production manually.

Every migration must be version controlled.

==========================================================
BUSINESS OWNERSHIP
==========================================================

Every table has one business owner.

Examples:

Customers module owns the Customers table.

Suppliers module owns the Suppliers table.

Projects module owns the Projects table.

Frontend pages never own database structures.

==========================================================
DATABASE EVOLUTION
==========================================================

The database evolves with the business.

Never redesign approved structures without authorization.

Prefer evolution over replacement.

Protect existing data.

==========================================================
FINAL PRINCIPLE
==========================================================

The database is one of the most valuable assets of NEXOTFE.

Every table, every field and every relationship must faithfully represent the industrial business and remain maintainable for many years.